  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When you localize your app, you add localizations by choosing a language, and then,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "optionally, a region and script from Xcode’s menus. Apple recommends that you choose",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the most specific localization, not just the language. For example, if you only support",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "English and it is American English, choose English (United States) (en-US) instead",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "of English (en).",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In Xcode menus, you choose a human-readable name for a localization, but in the project",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and exported files, a language identifier understood by localizers specifies the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "language, region, and script. The Xcode Localization Catalog (a folder with a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".xcloc",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "file extension) uses the language identifier as the suffix, as in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "en.xcloc",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "de.xcloc",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " for the English and German catalog names, respectively.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For information about how the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Bundle",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " object finds the best match between the localizations",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "your app supports and the user’s language and region settings, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/bundle",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Understand-the-language-identifier",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Understand the language identifier",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "language identifier",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " is a compound syntax that represents a combination of a language,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "regional variant, and script. It contains a language code, and, optionally, a region",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "code, and a script code.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For a language used in many regions, use just the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "language code",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " that represents",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the language (",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "[language code]",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": "). For example, to specify Serbian, use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "sr",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " language",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "code. Use the two-letter ISO 639-1 standard (preferred) or, if no code is available",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "for a particular language, use the ISO 639-2 standard instead.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To distinguish between different languages and regional variants, use a language",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "code with a region code separated by hyphens (",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "[language code]-[region code]",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": "). A",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "region code",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " represents a country or region. Use the ISO 3166-1 standard, a two-letter,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "capitalized code, such as, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "US",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GB",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "AU",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "FR",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". For example, to specify the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Swiss variant of the German language, use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "de-CH",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". If it’s not possible to create",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "a language identifier using the ISO 3166-1 standard, use the United Nations M.49",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "standard, which is a numeric code.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To specify a script, combine a language code with a script code in the ISO 3166-1",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "standard, separated by a hyphen (",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "[language code]-[script code]",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": "), as in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "az-Cyrl",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "for Azerbaijani in the Cyrillic script. To represent Chinese spoken in Taiwan and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "written in traditional Chinese script, use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "zh-Hant-TW",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "This table shows some common language identifiers with their language, region, and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
